Subject: Changelog Correlation Weight Net Source

Description: Raw preserved source for refining "net of weights" into a concrete data shape over changelog, narrative, and justification.

& [DictatedChangelogCorrelationWeightNetSource] is the preserved user source for weighted changelog correlation
  @ [user_statement] "did I mention a \"net of weights\" in correlation to a multi-dimensional hashmap of indications of subject-matter logically attached to the changelog to describe the attention to that subject."
  @ [user_statement] "I wonder if \"net of weights\" is just an ambiguous description I need to refine into a legitimate form of data..."
  @ [user_statement] "it's weighted correlations to the terms in the narrative tying together the change with the justification for the change by the narrative inspection."

  + [net_of_weights] is a candidate data shape for weighted attention over changelog-linked subject indications
  + [multi_dimensional_hashmap] is the semantic hash table and bucket space used to address components, terms, subjects, narrative, and evidence
  + [change_log_attachment] is the relation from changed files, hunks, roles, and commit bookends to subject-matter terms
  + [narrative_tie] is the relation from narrative terms to the meaning and purpose of the change
  + [justification_tie] is the relation from source, SJS, support, proof, or proposal records to why the change belongs
  + [legitimate_data_goal] is a concrete weighted correlation record that exposes evidence dimensions and residual outside

  = must: refine ambiguous weight language into inspectable data
  = must: keep repo delta as primary evidence and narrative as interpretive guide
  = must: keep justification/support separate from mere correlation heat
  - never: treat a weighted correlation as proof of motive or causal truth
